title: "DRMYN Studio: Metadata-Only AI-Assisted Movie Development and Production Workflow"
type: software
version: 0.18.0
date-released: 2026-06-04
repository-code: "https://github.com/hknbb/drmynstudio"
url: "https://github.com/hknbb/drmynstudio"
abstract: >
  DRMYN Studio is a metadata-only, schema-validated, human-gated research
  software framework for AI-assisted movie development and movie production
  process design, documentation, validation, and reproducibility. It provides
  canonical source records, planning metadata, prompt governance, JSON schema
  validation (20+ schemas, draft 2020-12), human approval workflows, evidence
  records, release manifests, and reproducibility infrastructure for AI-assisted
  film production processes. The repository also includes a three-agent
  autonomous orchestration layer (Claude Code / Codex / Gemini Code Assist)
  with auto-handoff and pickup mode enabling structured multi-agent coordination
  without external APIs. Generated media outputs are stored externally and
  referenced through metadata-only records. This v0.17.0 checkpoint formalizes
  the Element Reference Generation Policy v2: a two-stage Midjourney character
  reference chain (V8.1 narrative identity followed by V7 Omni Reference
  refinement), a scale-angle three-view pack replacing directional views
  (front_reference, three_quarter_medium_reference, three_quarter_close_reference),
  and non-character element routing through GPT Images 2. The v0.18.0 release adds the
  Scene Continuity System for Kling 3.0 Omni (O3): a deterministic beat-to-clip packer,
  a scene continuity ledger for inter-clip camera/action/screen-direction hand-off, an
  anti-clone figure roster (one distinct on-screen figure per @alias), a four-view
  scale-angle character reference policy with full-body look sheets, and a single
  canonical clip-manifest prompt path. Demonstrated through the Closing Price
  AI-assisted film project.
